Here are exact step-by-step instructions to open Adminer from your Trex box, using the same style as your project wiki.

âœ… This will allow you to directly inspect log_metadata_header, log_metadata_attr, and confirm your seed data.

âœ… 1. Find Adminer Port on Trex

On most Caterpillar / AT&T Trex dev-boxes, Adminer runs on:

localhost:8080


But sometimes:

8081, 8082, or 8090


Run this on Trex:

sudo netstat -tulpn | grep adminer


Or check running containers:

docker ps | grep adminer


Expected output example:

0.0.0.0:8080->8080/tcp   adminer


âœ… So Adminer is at port 8080 on Trex.

âœ… 2. SSH Port Forward From Your Windows Machine

Open PowerShell on your Windows laptop:

ssh -L 8080:localhost:8080 jenas7@10.224.82.10


Meaning:

Left 8080 = your local laptop port

Middle localhost:8080 = Adminer running on Trex

jenas7@10.224.82.10 = your Trex login

If Adminer is on a different port (8081, 8090), run:

ssh -L 8080:localhost:<ADMINER_PORT> jenas7@10.224.82.10


Example:

ssh -L 8080:localhost:8090 jenas7@10.224.82.10


âœ… Keep this SSH window open.
If you close it, the tunnel stops.

âœ… 3. Open Adminer in Browser

Now open:

ðŸ‘‰ http://localhost:8080

You should see the Adminer login screen.

âœ… 4. Login Credentials

Use the ones from your dev-box environment (~/dev-box/env, or /opt/db-service/config.env).

Typically:

System: MySQL
Server: oss-db-service
Database: cdcs


User / Password are stored here:

cat ~/dev-box/env


Look for lines like:

MYSQL_USER=awsadmin
MYSQL_PASSWORD=Initialpwdxxxxxxx
MYSQL_DATABASE=cdcs
MYSQL_HOST=oss-db-service


Use these in Adminer:

Field	Value
System	MySQL
Server	oss-db-service
Username	awsadmin
Password	Initialpwdxxxxxxx
Database	cdcs
